
Placky is simple Realtime network interface monitoring system.

It is meant as a simple web version of iptraf.

It consists of a simple Perl script, which is used to generate JSON data and a simple web page to display the current interface usage.

Live Demo can be found here: http://linux-bulgaria.org/placky.html

Requirements:
* Perl
* JSON::XS and CGI perl modules
* jQuery (it comes with 1.11.3)
* FlotCharts (it comes with 0.8.3)

Installation instructions:
  1. Simply unpack it, configure the directories in install.sh and run ./install.sh
  2. Then configure your server to serv the html and perl script.

